<TITLE> Minister receives SMS death threat </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 25 (bdnews24.com)Civil aviation minister GM Quader received a death threat by SMS on Tuesday. The SMS came from a Grameenphone number to the minister's cell number at around 2:30pm. "I have asked my personal secretary to file a complaint with the police," Quader told bdnews24.com. The message read, "Time and tide wait for none. But one person wait for you. Do you know who is he? He is Azrail. He must come and take your zaan. So, be careful. It is high time." Quader's personal secretary Abu Tayab told bdnews24.com, "I am going to file a general diary with the local police station".
